description: Deletes the specified message from the specified queue. To select the message to delete, use the ReceiptHandle of the message (not the MessageId which you receive when you send the message). Amazon SQS can delete a message from a queue even if a visibility timeout setting causes the message to be locked by another consumer. Amazon SQS automatically deletes messages left in a queue longer than the retention period configured for the queue.

parameters.name: QueueUrl
parameters.description: The URL of the Amazon SQS queue from which messages are deleted. Queue URLs and names are case-sensitive.

parameters.name: ReceiptHandle
parameters.description: The receipt handle associated with the message to delete.
